University-Wide Career AI Agent
README
Author: Marc-Anthony Jones
________________________________________
Overview
The University-Wide Career AI Agent is a structured career-support tool designed to assist students and early-career professionals across all majors, industries, and career levels.
Unlike traditional resume tools, this AI does not apply one-size-fits-all rules. Instead, it adapts guidance based on verified, discipline-specific standards and user-provided information.
Its role is to support decision-making, not replace student judgment or authorship.
________________________________________
Who This AI Is For
•	Undergraduate and graduate students
•	Interns and entry-level candidates
•	Early-career professionals
•	Users across all academic disciplines and industries
This tool is not limited to technical or STEM fields.
________________________________________
What the AI Can Help With
The Career AI Agent can assist with:
•	Resume guidance (discipline-aware)
•	Cover letter structure and review (with restrictions)
•	Role and location fit assessment
•	Interview preparation
•	Job compensation and offer analysis
All outputs are informational and supportive, not prescriptive.
________________________________________
Core Design Principles
1. No Universal Career Rules
There is no single resume format, page length, or career standard that applies to everyone.
The AI selects guidance only after identifying:
•	Major or field of study
•	Target role(s)
•	Industry
•	Career level
________________________________________
2. Verified Standards Only
Discipline-specific guidance is applied only when supported by verifiable sources, such as:
•	Professional associations
•	Licensing bodies
•	Accredited universities and career centers
•	Government labor data
•	Widely accepted academic guidelines
If a standard cannot be verified, the AI:
•	States the limitation
•	Avoids assumptions
•	Defaults to conservative guidance
•	Asks the user how to proceed
________________________________________
3. Ethical Use of AI
The AI:
•	Does not fabricate experience, credentials, or metrics
•	Does not assume GitHub, portfolios, licensure, or publications
•	Does not encourage deception or misrepresentation
Students remain responsible for all submitted materials.
________________________________________
Cover Letter Policy (Important)
Cover letters are often reviewed by humans and may be used to detect AI-generated writing.
For this reason, the AI:
•	Provides structure, talking points, and review only
•	Does not generate final submission-ready cover letters
•	Emphasizes student authorship and personal voice
Submitting AI-generated cover letters verbatim may result in rejection.
________________________________________
How Inputs Are Handled
Users may upload:
•	One consolidated experience file
or
•	Multiple files (resume, LinkedIn, portfolio, transcript, etc.)
The AI will:
•	Merge all uploads into a single internal profile
•	Remove duplicates
•	Use only verified, user-provided information
No experience is invented or inferred.
________________________________________
Fit Scoring & Compensation Analysis
•	Fit scores range from 0–100
•	Scoring criteria adapt by discipline
•	Explanations are provided only if requested
Compensation guidance:
•	Uses verified data when available
•	Avoids speculation
•	Is informational, not advisory
________________________________________
Quick Commands Supported
Users may use the following commands:
•	/resume – Resume guidance or generation (standards first)
•	/coverletter – Structure and review guidance only
•	/fit – Role or location fit assessment
•	/interview – Interview preparation by field and role
•	/offer – Job offer and compensation analysis
•	/standards – View which standards are being applied
•	/intake – Run full clarification intake
Commands do not bypass governance rules.
________________________________________
What This AI Is Not
•	Not a resume template generator
•	Not a career decision-maker
•	Not a substitute for advisors, faculty, or employers
•	Not a source of guaranteed outcomes
________________________________________
Key Takeaway
The University-Wide Career AI Agent is designed to be:
Adaptive. Ethical. Verified. Student-centered.
It helps users understand expectations, evaluate options, and prepare responsibly—while leaving final decisions and authorship where they belong: with the student.

